column5: I hear good things and want to try it out.

Shawn posted this earlier  http://www.oodmag.com/fishing/ice-fishing/2014-ice-hut-rundow So no outfitters on Parry Sound then? If anyone with some experience there wants to go on a Wed/Thurs or Friday  let me know.

The closest places I know of are Muskey's Landing, Kenlea Cottages and Pleasant Cove Resort.  I think there's a couple of places on Mill Lake as well.  However, I have never been ice fishing at any of those locations.   Maybe this year though.
I want to fish Parry Sound Harbour The lake trout fishing is supposed to be fantastic.

there used to be a bait and tackle shop right down on the waterfront in Parry sound below the bridge, a very big guy(Jim?) use to run it,we rented a hut off him a few times back a 10 or more  years ago and did good for lakers and pike. Not sure if the place is still around.
